  "prompt": "What is the meaning of Urdu words 'Lafz' and 'Alfaaz'?",
  "response": "In Urdu, the words **'Lafz'** (\u0644\u0641\u0638) and **'Alfaaz'** (\u0627\u0644\u0641\u0627\u0638) are related to language and speech. Here's their meaning:\n\n1. **Lafz (\u0644\u0641\u0638)**: This word means **\"word\"** or **\"term\"** in English. It refers to a single unit of language that carries meaning.\n\n2. **Alfaaz (\u0627\u0644\u0641\u0627\u0638)**: This is the plural form of 'Lafz', meaning **\"words\"** or **\"vocabulary\"**. It is used when referring to multiple words or a collection of terms.\n\nFor example:\n- \"Yeh lafz ka matlab kya hai?\" (What does this word mean?)  \n- \"Unke alfaaz bohot gehray thay.\" (Their words were very profound.)  \n\nBoth are commonly used in everyday conversations, poetry, and literature in Urdu.",
